# Component Conventions

This repo is an early-stage UI reference for Pax Historia. Build in any order — no design-system phases.

## Rules

1. **One file = one component** in its own folder when non-trivial: `components/SettingRow/SettingRow.tsx`
2. **Props-first:** put anything that can change into props (label, icon, onClick, variant, isActive)
3. **Composition:** compose screens from small components; avoid 400-line monolith JSX
4. **Hard-code first, extract later:** a hex color in a component is OK; extract to a CSS variable or `variant` prop after 3+ repeats
5. **Theme:** use Tailwind `dark:` and CSS variables in `globals.css` when colors stabilize — not required on day one
6. **Responsive — desktop-first:** desktop layout in base classes; overrides via `max-xl:`, `max-lg:`, `max-md:` (not mobile-first `sm:` as default)
7. **Custom components only** — no HeroUI, shadcn, or other UI libraries
8. **No pre-built stubs** — add components only when building a real screen

## Stack reminders

- TypeScript, Next.js App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, `motion`, `next-themes`
- Font: Poppins only (via `next/font`)
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/cn` for class names
- Add `'use client'` when using motion or browser-only APIs

## When advising

Do not impose token/component phases. Suggest extraction only when a pattern repeats. Reference screenshots in `docs/reference/`.
